# Keep the build context small & the image clean. Anything the Dockerfile
# doesn't COPY is excluded anyway, but trimming the context speeds up the
# `docker build` upload and avoids leaking local cruft.
# NOTE: .dockerignore does NOT support inline comments — a `#` only starts a
# comment at the beginning of a line. Keep patterns on their own lines.
.venv/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
.git/
.github/
.dvc/
data/
tests/
mlruns/
mlflow.db
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
htmlcov/
coverage.xml
# Exclude docs, then re-include the one file pyproject's `readme` field needs.
*.md
!README.md
